The paper discusses the design of a neuromorphic processor for online learning using spiking neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of event-based processing for vision and sensorimotor control, which could fall under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the processor for classification tasks, which could fall under cs.AR (Augmented Reality) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses the MNIST dataset for testing, which is commonly used in computer vision, suggesting a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
